    "course_title": "STORYTELLING ON STAGE: INTRODUCTION TO MUSICAL THEATER AND OPERA",
    "description": "Introduction to musical theater and opera in Europe and America, with emphasis on the ways creators tell their stories through the interaction of music and drama. Topics include the histories and formations of the genres and their relationships to culture and society; principal creators and performers; distinctive features of representative works; relationships to film and other media; and treatments of race, class, gender, and other issues in selected examples of each genre.",
